#Text=DS : Has the Iraq War affected you at all ?
#Text=RP :
#Text=Absolutely .
#Text=It ’s not good , I do n’t like it , and it makes me want to enjoy this moment a lot more and be very appreciative .
#Text=Like when I ’m on a hike in a canyon and it smells good and there are n’t bombs dropping .
#Text=DS : Do you think there is a lot of apathy in the culture ?
#Text=RP :
#Text=There ’s apathy , and there ’s a lot of anti-depressants and that probably lends a big contribution to the apathy .
#Text=We have iPods and GPS systems and all these things to distract us .
#Text=DS : Do you ever work the current political culture into your art ?
#Text=RP :
#Text=No , I do n’t .
#Text=Every time I bat my eyelashes it ’s a political statement .
#Text=The drag I come from has always been a critique of our society , so the act is defiant in and of itself in a patriarchal society such as ours .
#Text=It ’s an act of treason .
#Text=DS : What do you think of young performance artists working in drag today ?
#Text=RP :
#Text=I do n’t know of any .
#Text=I do n’t know of any .
#Text=Because the gay culture is obsessed with everything straight and femininity has been under attack for so many years , there are n’t any up and coming drag artists .
#Text=Gay culture is n’t paying attention to it , and straight people do n’t either .
#Text=There are n’t any drag clubs to go to in New York .
#Text=I see more drag clubs in Los Angeles than in New York , which is so odd because L.A. has never been about club culture .
#Text=DS : Michael Musto told me something that was opposite of what you said .
#Text=He said he felt that the younger gays , the ones who are up-and-coming , are over the body fascism and more willing to embrace their feminine sides .
#Text=RP :
#Text=I think they are redefining what femininity is , but I still think there is a lot of negativity associated with true femininity .
#Text=Do boys wear eyeliner and dress in skinny jeans now ?
#Text=Yes , they do .

#Text=But it ’s still a heavily patriarchal culture and you never see two men in Star magazine , or the Queer Eye guys at a premiere , the way you see Ellen and her girlfriend — where they are all , ‘ Oh , look how cute ’ — without a negative connotation to it .
#Text=There is a definite prejudice towards men who use femininity as part of their palette ; their emotional palette , their physical palette .
#Text=Is that changing ?
#Text=It ’s changing in ways that do n’t advance the cause of femininity .
#Text=I ’m not talking frilly-laced pink things or Hello Kitty stuff .
#Text=I ’m talking about goddess energy , intuition and feelings .
#Text=That is still under attack , and it has gotten worse .
#Text=That ’s why you would n’t get someone covering the RuPaul album , or why they say people are n’t tuning into the Katie Couric show .

#Text=Sure , they can say ‘ Oh , RuPaul ’s album sucks ’ and ‘ Katie Couric is awful ’ ; but that ’s not really true . It ’s about what our culture finds important , and what ’s important are things that support patriarchal power .
#Text=The only feminine thing supported in this struggle is Pamela Anderson and Jessica Simpson , things that support our patriarchal culture .
